<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-615-115  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 615 115.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  Nov 12 1990 v36 n1835 p25(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Rack mount 3480 vendors target stations, nets. (manufacturers ofrack-mountable 3480 tape drives target workstations and networks)(Spotlight on Disk andamp; Tape Drives special section)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Zipper, Stuart.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The slowdown in the midrange computer market has causedmanufacturers of rack-mountable 3480 tape drives to targetworkstations and networks to increase sales.andP;  Rack-mount drivesare smaller and less expensive than floor-standing versions; theyare manufactured by Storage Technology Corp, Fujitsu, Philipssubsidiary Laser Magnetic Storage and Cipher.andP;  The companies hopeto account for 25 percent of the overall tape storage devicemarket, which is estimated to be worth between $2 billion and $2.5billion annually.andP;  Analysts point out that the market forrack-mount 3480 tape drives has grown more slowly than expected,due in part a general slowdown in the economy, but also to thefailure of IBM or DEC to deliver a rack-mount 3480.andP;  Among theproducts described are StorageTek's 4280 subsystem, Cipher'sTapeXpress, Laser Magnetic Storage's Independence and Fujitsu'sM2480.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Tape DrivesMarket AnalysisManufacturersMarketing Strategy.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>